<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-02-19T06:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-02-19T06:00:00-05:00" n="117" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d117">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72112/7018</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_SWG1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Sharp</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-02-19T11:00:00+00:00">
                                        <hi rend="italic">February 19, 1918, 11 a.m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                    <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 4.32 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>3214. Note received from Foreign Office stating that it attaches
                                great importance to closer cooperation among principal Allies in
                                preparing, establishing, and applying black list and in order to
                                avoid delays in exchange of communications between these Governments
                                it desires that an American, French, and English representative be
                                designated in each capital to discuss with competent services all
                                questions relating to the black list. The French Government
                                requests, in case proposition is adopted, that a member of Embassy
                                be designated to enter into direct relations with service of black
                                lists of Ministry of Blockade. I would appreciate being informed of
                                reply which I may make. Foreign Office note follows by next
                                pouch.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_SWG1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Sharp</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>